{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Meringue","content":["Preheat oven to 150°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place sugar and cornflour in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>5 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites, salt and lemon juice in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, whip <nobr>4 min\/37°C\/speed 3<\/nobr> while slowly adding reserved sugar mixture through hole in mixing bowl lid.","With the help of a spoon, place meringue on prepared tray in a circle shape then bake for 10 minutes (150°C). Turn oven down to 120°C and continue baking for 1 hour (120°C), or until set. Turn off oven and allow meringue to cool inside without opening the door (approx. 3-4 hours or overnight). Clean and dry mixing bowl and make topping."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Place peaches, honey, water and wine in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Drain through simmering basket, discarding cooking liquid and set aside to cool. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Once meringue has cooled, remove from baking paper to a serving plate. <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place cream in mixing bowl and whip <nobr>without setting a time\/speed 3<\/nobr> until softly whipped, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping. Cover meringue with whipped cream then top with reserved cooled, cooked peaches. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Meringue","content":["220 g sugar","1 Tbsp cornflour","4 egg whites, from large eggs","1 pinch salt","1 tsp lemon juice"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["350 g peaches, stoned and cut in slices (1 cm)","20 g honey","150 g water","50 g moscatel wine","400 g whipping cream"]}],"id":"r178990","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-2yrZ0XK8eEo\/XZWdssIDSmI\/AAAAAAAAepM\/3chfwGfN3TszbBcuIxd7pTpf7EoiZSJYQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LTnpkB26HCS_mszx.png","title":"Peach pavlova","publishedAt":"2018-04-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"17 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"34 g","calories":"1287 kJ \/ 308 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and baking paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The meringue and peaches can be made ahead. Whip the cream and assemble the finished dish just before serving."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","5h 30m","8 portions"]}